---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const questions = [
  {
    category: 'Love & Relationships',
    items: [
      'What makes Vick and Ann\'s relationship so transgressive in the context of Pagua Bay? Which social barriers are most powerful: race, class, or family expectation?',
      'How does the community\'s reaction to Vick and Ann\'s relationship reflect broader patterns of how societies police who can love whom?',
      'Do you think Vick and Ann were naive about the consequences of their relationship, or bravely defiant? Where is the line between the two?',
    ],
  },
  {
    category: 'Truth & Justice',
    items: [
      'Why does the village choose silence over truth after the fire? What are the costs and benefits of that silence for different characters?',
      'Ma Peacock takes enormous personal risk to seek the truth. What drives her when everyone else looks away? Have you ever been in a situation where speaking up was costly?',
      'The novel suggests that some truths, once buried, poison an entire community. Do you agree? Can you think of real-world parallels?',
    ],
  },
  {
    category: 'Culture & Identity',
    items: [
      'How does Ann\'s Kalinago heritage shape her experience in the village? How does the novel portray the relationship between the Kalinago community and the wider village?',
      'What role does obeah play in the story? How does the novel navigate the line between superstition and spiritual tradition?',
      'The Nine Night vigil is both a funeral tradition and the setting for key revelations. How does the ritual structure shape the story\'s pacing and emotional impact?',
    ],
  },
  {
    category: 'Power & Privilege',
    items: [
      'How does the Dorado family\'s wealth influence the investigation, and the village\'s willingness to question the official story?',
      'Ma Dorado is both a complex character and a formidable antagonist. Did you find yourself understanding her perspective, even while opposing her actions?',
      'The novel depicts a community where power is held by a few families. How does this dynamic shape who gets to speak, who gets to love, and who gets justice?',
    ],
  },
  {
    category: 'Language & Voice',
    items: [
      'The novel uses Dominican Creole alongside English. How did this affect your reading experience? What did the Creole add that English alone couldn\'t convey?',
      'Many characters speak in distinct voices, from the village elders to the young generation. Which voice stayed with you most, and why?',
      'How does the oral storytelling tradition of the Caribbean shape the novel\'s structure and style?',
    ],
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Book Clubs"
  description="Discussion questions and resources for book clubs reading Secrets of Pagua Bay by Deborah Balthazar."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative pt-32 pb-20 sm:pt-40 sm:pb-28 ambient-bg overflow-hidden">
    <div class="relative max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <p class="text-amber text-sm tracking-widest uppercase mb-4 font-medium section-fade">Book Clubs</p>
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-6xl text-salt mb-6 section-fade">
        Discussion<br />
        <span class="text-amber italic">Guide</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-salt/60 max-w-2xl mx-auto section-fade">
        Whether you're reading alone or with a group, these questions are designed to
        deepen your experience of the novel and spark meaningful conversation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Questions -->
  <section class="py-20 sm:py-28 bg-charcoal">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="space-y-12">
        {questions.map((section, sectionIdx) => (
          <div class="section-fade">
            <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-amber mb-6">{section.category}</h2>
            <ol class="space-y-4" start={sectionIdx * 3 + 1}>
              {section.items.map((q, i) => (
                <li class="flex gap-4 text-salt/80 leading-relaxed">
                  <span class="text-amber/40 font-display text-lg shrink-0 w-8">
                    {sectionIdx * 3 + i + 1}.
                  </span>
                  <span>{q}</span>
                </li>
              ))}
            </ol>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <!-- Tips -->
      <div class="mt-20 section-fade">
        <div class="p-8 bg-midnight/50 border border-salt/10 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-salt mb-4">Tips for Your Book Club</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-salt/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber mt-0.5">•</span>
              <span>Set the mood with Caribbean music. Look for Dominican cadence-lypso or bouyon playlists.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber mt-0.5">•</span>
              <span>Serve ti-punch (white rum, lime, cane sugar) or sorrel drink for an authentic island atmosphere.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber mt-0.5">•</span>
              <span>Read select passages aloud in the Creole. The rhythm and cadence add a dimension that silent reading can't capture.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber mt-0.5">•</span>
              <span>Visit the <a href="/the-world#glossary" class="text-amber hover:underline">glossary</a> before your meeting to familiarize yourself with the Creole terms.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Contact for Book Clubs -->
  <section class="py-20 sm:py-28 bg-midnight text-center">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 section-fade">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-salt mb-4">Invite the Author</h2>
      <p class="text-salt/60 mb-8">
        Deborah is available for virtual book club visits and Q&A sessions. Reach out
        through the <a href="/press" class="text-amber hover:underline">press page</a>
        to arrange a visit.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
